The paper focuses on machine learning algorithms, specifically supervised and semi-supervised learning for image classification tasks. The paper introduces a new regularization technique called self-supervised regularization and compares its effectiveness with traditional supervised classifiers and state-of-the-art consistency baselines. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
